<h2>About</h2>
<p2>I grew up in the City of Champions, Pittsburgh, PA with an appropriate last name. My formative years consisted of a lot of reading and a lot of athletics. At the age of 18, I matriculated to Winston-Salem, NC for four years of studying at Wake Forest University. Wake offers a liberal arts education, so while majoring in finance there was plenty of Anthropology, Philosphy, Politics, and Biology. This wholistic view of the world left a strong impression and contributed to a life of learning. After gradaution I made my way to the Windy City, where I embarked on a career as a Credit Investor, while continuing to read, learn and try new things like breakdancing, improv, meditation, common books, float tanks, beach volleyball, hoops, biking, hiking, and learning Spanish (ok, so my wife is from Mexico, so this might not have been entirely a self motivated activity). Now I'm married to an amazing wife, while continuing the journey of life long learning and attempting to excell at investing. 
</p2>
